  "text": "Firefox NSS TLS/SSL Implementation Audit Results:\n\n1. **ssl3con.c** (github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8, security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3con.c)\n   - Protocol: SSL3 Protocol (TLS 1.0-1.2)\n   - Primary Function: ssl3_HandleRecord (line 13721) - Implements core SSL 3.0/TLS record processing\n   - Features: Record decryption, cipher suite negotiation, handshake message handling, master secret derivation\n   - Key Functions: ssl3_ComputeMasterSecret, ssl3_DeriveConnectionKeys, ssl3_SendRecord, ssl3_InitHandshakeHashes\n\n2. **tls13con.c** (github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8, security/nss/lib/ssl/tls13con.c)\n   - Protocol: TLS 1.3 Protocol\n   - Primary Functions: tls13_FinishHandshake (line 5982), tls13_SendClientSecondFlight (line 6005)\n   - Features: TLS 1.3 handshake state machine, key derivation (HKDF), encrypted extensions, post-handshake messages\n   - Key Functions: tls13_SetCipherSpec, tls13_SendServerHelloSequence, tls13_HandleClientKeyShare, tls13_SendHelloRetryRequest\n   - HKDF Labels: Traffic secrets, finished secrets, resumption master secret, exporter secret\n\n3. **dtlscon.c** (github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8, security/nss/lib/ssl/dtlscon.c)\n   - Protocol: DTLS Protocol (Datagram TLS)\n   - Primary Functions: ssl3_DisableNonDTLSSuites (line 108), dtls_AllocQueuedMessage (line 123)\n   - Features: DTLS record processing, handshake message queuing, retransmission timer management, out-of-order message handling\n   - Key Functions: dtls_FreeHandshakeMessage, dtls_FreeHandshakeMessages, dtls_RetransmitDetected, dtls_StartRetransmitTimer\n   - Note: Maps DTLS versions to TLS versions, disables non-DTLS cipher suites (RC4, stream ciphers)\n\n4. **ssl3ecc.c** (github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8, security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3ecc.c)\n   - Protocol: SSL3 Protocol (ECC-specific implementation)\n   - Primary Function: ssl3_SendECDHClientKeyExchange (line 165)\n   - Features: ECC cipher suite operations, elliptic curve key exchange, EC parameter conversion\n   - Key Functions: ssl_NamedGroup2ECParams, ssl3_ComputeECDHKeyHash, ssl_ECDHEKeyExchange\n   - Note: ECC code moved here from ssl3con.c for modularity\n\n5. **sslexp.h** (github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8, security/nss/lib/ssl/sslexp.h)\n   - Type: Header file declaring experimental SSL APIs\n   - Primary Purpose: Experimental function prototypes and extension hooks\n   - Features: Custom extension hooks (SSLExtensionWriter, SSLExtensionHandler), SSL_GetExtensionSupport, SSL_EXPERIMENTAL_API macro\n   - Note: Functions in this header are not guaranteed to remain available in future NSS versions\n\nAll files are located in the Firefox NSS library security/nss/lib/ssl/ directory within repository github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8. These files implement the core TLS protocol stack including SSL 3.0/TLS 1.0-1.2, TLS 1.3, DTLS, and ECC cipher suite handling."
}

